wart an instant billionaire she served as president chairwoman and ceo of the company until being forced to resign as a result of the imclone insider trading case as part of an agreement with the sec she was banned from serving in any role that would allow her to prepare audit or disclose financial results of a public company until august  in effect this banned her from serving as an officer of her own company however she still owns a  percent controlling interest stewart rejoined the board of directors of her namesake company in september  and became its chairwoman once again in may  on december   it was announced that sequential brands group acquired martha stewart living omnimedia as a result of its acquisition martha stewart living omnimedia requested that the new york stock exchange nyse suspend trading  delist the companys common stock corporate executivesedit sheraton kalouria as president of television daniel dienst chief executive officer and director as of  publishingedit martha stewart living martha stewart weddings special issues including the annual holiday cookies blueprint canceled martha stewart kids canceled martha stewart baby canceled everyday food canceled whole living canceled four newspaper columns — ask martha living weddings and everyday food — are distributed to newspapers throughout the united states via the new york times syndicate current books are published through random houses clarkson potter division earlier titles were offered through subsidiaries of time warner prior to stewarts spinoff of her business ventures from its corporate umbrella publishing activities are a major source of income for the company and accounted for roughly  of total revenue in  television and radioedit televisionedit on  november  martha stewart named nbcs sheraton kalouria as president of television for martha stewart living omnimedia mslo he was responsible for development and production of global programming for cable broadcast syndication and dvd as well as managing mslos development in the area of digital content for video on demand web and mobile platforms martha syndicated daily everyday food pbs weekly martha stewart living from marthas kitchen although mslo retained no technical ownership stake in nbcs program the apprentice martha stewart the company its magazines and various business ventures were prominently featured in each episode mark burnett who produced the series is also coproducer of the companys daily talk show martha dvdedit mslo began marketing instructional dvds in late  through a partnership with warner bros with the first five offerings oriented toward cooking and holiday and special event planning radioedit mslo operates a satellite radio channel martha stewart living radio on channel  of siriusxm satellite radio among programs on the channel there was a weekdayevening talk show cohosted by martha stewarts daughter alexis stewart whatever with alexis and jennifer alexis left the radio show in june  leaving jennifer koppelmanhutt as the sole host the show was cancelled in december  and koppelmanhutt was terminated internet and direct commerceedit the companys internet and direct commerce segment currently includes its website marthastewartcom and a direct to consumer flower business marthastewartflowerscom through an agreement with touchpoint it designed a line of customizable greeting cards under the marthascards banner which were sourced and fulfilled by touchpoint this agreement was replaced by a new program with kodak easyshare gallery in  in november  mslo announced their launch of marthas circle which is a lifestyle oriented blog adnetwork whose charter members include apartment therapy smitten kitchen and charles  hudson historically the company also produced a print and online catalog martha by mail which was launched in  and later rebranded as martha stewart the catalog for living following stewarts public fallout and the dotcom bubble burst in  the company decided to discontinue both the online and print editions in  the final print catalog was mailed in january  and the online store closed in june of that year merchandisingedit mslo additionally offers various home goods through its massmarket martha stewart everyday brand in kmart stores throughout the united states and at sears canada in canada furniture and paint are part of the companys specialtyretail oriented martha stewart signature brand through a partnership with bernhardt furniture company and previously with sherwinwilliams in october  the company announced a new agreement with lowes to develop an exclusive interior paints line which replaced its previous contract with sherwinwilliams the new line of paints martha stewart colors launched in april  in april  the company also announced its plans to develop a new upmarket merchandise line with macys inc at the time named federated department stores launched in macys stores in  the company has also announced its intention to design a new paperbased crafts product line martha stewart crafts with ek success initially planned for release in time for the holiday  season which later debuted in early  at michaels stores in fall of  stewart announced the development of a line of outdoor furniture indoor organization kitchen cabinets and decor products at home depot on december   jcpenney announced the acquisition of  percent of the companys stock jcpenney plans to put minimartha stewart shops in many of its stores in  as well as starting a web site together wineedit on september   martha stewart living omnimedia announced that it inked a partnership with e  j gallo winery to produce a wine brand with the label martha stewart vintage for sale in  cities january the  cases to be sold include  sonoma county chardonnay  sonoma county cabernet sauvignon and  sonoma county merlot for atlanta boston charlotte north carolina denver phoenix and portland oregon martha stewart also signed a contract with costco wholesale corp to offer a series of food products developed from mslo’s library of recipes acquisition of emeril lagasse franchiseedit on february   msl omnimedia announced that the company had reached an agreement with celebrity chef emeril lagasse to purchase certain business assets for  million  million in cash and  million in stock with the exclusion of emeril lagasse’s restaurant chain and his foundation the deal consists of the rights to television programs such as essence of emeril and emeril live emeril lagasse’s cookbook library the emerilscom website and kitchen and food products controversiesedit investors lawsuitedit on august   a class action was filed against martha stewart living omnimedia inc for misleading investors by issuing materially false and misleading statements and its officers using insider information to avoid losses a settlement of  million was approved in  in  the company previously recognized as expense its estimate of annualsubscriptionacquisition costs ratably throughout the year after reviewing this matter with its independent certified public accounting firm and its auditcommittee the company determined on october   to change the method of accounting for interim period expense recognition of its subscription acquisition costs the company recognized subscriptionacquisition costs in the period in which the acquisition efforts took place and restated the financial statements macys lawsuitedit in december  macys sued martha stewart and penney after the two companies decided in  to partner up and open up what would be called martha stewart home shops macys sued martha stewart for breach of contract and sued penney for interfering with its agreement with martha stewart both of these lawsuits were combined in december  macys goal was to stop penney from selling martha stewart merchandise that was supposed to be sold exclusively at macys macys settled a portion of its lawsuit with martha stewart omnimedia over a home products deal however macys continues to sue jc penney company inc stewart did not disclose the terms of the settlement this lawsuit cost between  million and  million in legal costs according to ceo dienst referencesedit  a b c d e f martha stewart living omnimedia inc securities and exchange commission february    company overview marthastewartcom archived from the original on  retrieved    lockwood lisa april   martha stewart touting american made wwd retrieved  august    securities and exchange commission litigation release no   august   securities and exchange commission retrieved    martha stewart rejoins her board new york times september     martha stewart named nonexecutive chairman of namesake company wall street journal may     a b martha stewart living omnimedia announces closing of merger with sequential brands group wwwprnewswirecom pr newswire retrieved  december    sequential brands group signs definitive merger agreement to acquire martha stewart living omnimedia martha stewart living omnimedia retrieved  june  permanent dead link  a b c d steigrad alexandra  february  mslos new ceo daniel dienst hits reset wwd retrieved  february    eggerton john  may  mslo taps more former abc execs broadcastingcablecom retrieved  october    thielman sam  october  stewart to launch vod service varietycom retrieved  october    mslo draws marthas circle blog lifestyle site network mediaweekcom retrieved    jc penney to offer martha stewart shops winstonsalem journal associated press  retrieved  permanent dead link  martha stewart buys emeril franchise associated press business news usmso  msn moneydead link  class action lawsuit against mso archived from the original on    qa martha stewart living omnimedia inc   a b alawadhi neha  january  martha stewart macys settle lawsuit over penney deal reuters retrieved  january    cho janet  october  jcpenney agrees only macys can sell some martha stewart items cleveland retrieved  january    clark evan  january  macys settles with martha stewart wwd retrieved  january   external linksedit o