ry the emerilscom website and kitchen and food products controversiesedit investors lawsuitedit on august   a class action was filed against martha stewart living omnimedia inc for misleading investors by issuing materially false and misleading statements and its officers using insider information to avoid losses a settlement of  million was approved in  in  the company previously recognized as expense its estimate of annualsubscriptionacquisition costs ratably throughout the year after reviewing this matter with its independent certified public accounting firm and its auditcommittee the company determined on october   to change the method of accounting for interim period expense recognition of its subscription acquisition costs the company recognized subscriptionacquisition costs in the period in which the acquisition efforts took place and restated the financial statements macys lawsuitedit in december  macys sued martha stewart and penney after the two companies decided in  to partner up and open up what would be called martha stewart home shops macys sued martha stewart for breach of contract and sued penney for interfering with its agreement with martha stewart both of these lawsuits were combined in december  macys goal was to stop penney from selling martha stewart merchandise that was supposed to be sold exclusively at macys macys settled a portion of its lawsuit with martha stewart omnimedia over a home products deal however macys continues to sue jc penney company inc stewart did not disclose the terms of the settlement this lawsuit cost between  million and  million in legal costs according to ceo dienst referencesedit  a b c d e f martha stewart living omnimedia inc securities and exchange commission february    company overview marthastewartcom archived from the original on  retrieved    lockwood lisa april   martha stewart touting american made wwd retrieved  august    securities and exchange commission litigation release no   august   securities and e