el and skincare blame martha stewart for yankees ruined perfect game martha stewart launches virtual wine store the rivalry between domestic diva martha stewart and gwyneth paltrow amped up monday when the oscarwinning actress hired lisa gersh to be the ceo of goop her fledgling lifestyle and ecommerce company gersh is the former chief of martha stewart living omnimedia who exited in early  after only a year on the job paltrow  has been using the yearold goop to move slowly but steadily into stewart’s sweet spot — that is handing out advice on home food and fashion in fact goop which paltrow and gersh prefer to present with a lowercase “g” sometimes publishes recipes adapted from stewart stewart  has been curtly dismissive of paltrow’s efforts to crack the personal lifestyle multimedia genre that stewart has pioneered with books magazines web properties and tv shows in a recent interview stewart said paltrow should pipe down and stick to acting “she just needs to be quiet” stewart was quoted as telling netaporter’s porter magazine “she’s a movie star if she were confident in her acting she wouldn’t be trying to be martha stewart” paltrow started goop in london but recently moved the company to the us and is clearly intent on expanding what has been a moneylosing ecommerce company “lisa is a visionary leader with unparalleled creativity and savvy” paltrow said in making the announcement “she’s the perfect person to build on the momentum we have already created at goop and to diversify our opportunities to bring goop’s positive energy directly to consumers in what they read what they try and what they buy and how they live” gersh  who worked at nbc before mslo and cofounded oxygen media hinted that part of her job at goop would be to bring new products to market but she did not say if any of those new products would be a magazine moving into print would make paltrow even more of a rival to stewart “building on goop’s unique success we’ll continue to invest in the company expand globally and launch next product lines and partnerships the future of commerce is all tied to best in class trusted distinctive curated content” goop had  revenues of  million and posted a loss of  in that year according to documents on file with companies house in britain which tracks corporate results paltrow and goop’s previous ceo sebastian bishop who left earlier this year pulled in combined salaries of almost  in  the last year for which figures are available the filing for  is overdue according to companies house with its move to the us goop recently incorporated in new york goop also recently engaged in a legal battle with charles plotkin a hunter college professor and nutritional guru over its use of the “diet detective” phrase that plotkin claims the company used without permission the suit filed in manhattan state court was recently settled according to plotkin who on monday declined to divulge details goop also contributed about  to three charities the sandy hook foundation the pencils of promise and the edible schoolyard project share thisfacebooktwittergooglefacebook messengerwhatsappemailcopy filed under gwyneth paltrow   martha stewart   martha stewart living omnimedia share this article share thisfacebooktwittergooglefacebook messengerwhatsappemailcopy read next zucker has no comcast regrets read next zucker has no comcast regrets share selection trending nowon nypostcom  man ordered to pay k in child support for kid who isnt his  i f—king killed my sister teen livestreams fatal car crash  this tech company will start microchipping their workers now on younger ‘modern family’ castmates getting over k per episode scott disick’s bevy of bikini babes and more star snaps justin bieber abruptly cancels rest of world tour see all video  michael jacksons former pet chimp is now a professional artist now on ‘game of thrones’ five things you may have missed from season  episode  “stormborn” see all more stories page six morning joe staffers losing